iversity of »discovered« educational realities. In the process, many basic assumptions have turned into genuine tasks of research. Where are the places and times of learning, education, and social work to be found? Who are the actors and addressees? How are education and learning performed and enacted?The contributions to this volume discuss the multiple challenges that ethnographic research has to confront when exploring the multimodality, plurality, and translocality of educational realities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEducational anthropologyxResearch. 0aEthnologyxResearch. 0aLearningxResearch. 0aSocial work education. 4aEducation. 4aEducational Research. 4aMethodology. 4aMultimodality. 4aPedagogy. 4aResearch. 4aSociology of Education. 4aSociomateriality. 4aTheory of Education. 4aTranslocality. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aEducation.  aEducational Research.  aMethodology.  aMultimodality.  aPedagogy.  aResearch.  aSociology of Education.  aSociomateriality.  aTheory of Education.  aTranslocality.1 aBollig, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBollig, Sabine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoyle, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFairbanks, Robert P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenwick, Tara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonig, Michael-Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonig, Michael-Sebastian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aImoto, Yuki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelle, Helga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular